data.title: Biography of Louis Bourbon Duke Brittany 1704-1705
data.meta_description: Biography of Louis Bourbon Duke Brittany 1704-1705 including his birth, marriages, death and life events, life events of his siblings, and his ancestry to five generations, royal ancestors and royal descendants.
data.text:
Louis Bourbon Duke Brittany was appointed Duke Brittany.

On 25 Jun 1704 Louis Bourbon Duke Brittany was born to Louis Bourbon Duke Burgundy 1682-1712 (age 21) and Maria Adelaide Savoy (age 18). He a great x 2 grandson of King Charles I of England, Scotland and Ireland. Coefficient of inbreeding 5.82%.

On 13 Apr 1705 Louis Bourbon Duke Brittany died.

[his father] Louis Bourbon Duke Burgundy 1682-1712 and [his mother] Maria Adelaide Savoy were married. She the daughter of Victor Amadeus King Sardinia and Anne Marie Bourbon Queen Consort Sardinia 1669-1728. He the son of Louis "Le Grand Dauphin" Bourbon Duke Burgundy and Maria Anna Victoria Wittelsbach Duchess Burgundy 1660-1690. They were second cousins. She a great granddaughter of King Charles I of England, Scotland and Ireland.
